The '''2026 Austrian Grand Prix''' included a sprint weekend.

== Sprint qualifying ==
Lando Norris took pole for the sprint shootout.

== Sprint ==
Oscar Piastri won the sprint from pole. Max Verstappen received a five-second penalty on lap 12 for impeding.

== Qualifying ==
Norris took pole for the race. Ferrari were 0.3 seconds off the front row.

== Race ==
Norris led from the start and won the race. A safety car was deployed on lap 28 after Lance Stroll retired with an engine failure on lap 27.

